SIMPLE: spend
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spend
<hw>Spend</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Spent</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Spending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>spendan</ets> (in
comp.), fr. L. <ets>expendere</ets> or <ets>dispendere</ets> to weigh
out, to expend, dispense. See <er>Pendant</er>, and cf.
<er>Dispend</er>, <er>Expend</er>, <er>Spence</er>,
<er>Spencer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To weigh or lay out; to
dispose of; to part with; <as>as, to <ex>spend</ex> money for
clothing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Spend</qex> thou that in the town.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherefore do ye <qex>spend</qex> money for that which is not
bread?</q> <rj><qau>Isa. lv. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1383 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bestow; to employ; -- often with <xex>on</xex> or
<xex>upon</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I . . . am never loath⟦br⟧
To <qex>spend</qex> my judgment.</q> <rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To consume; to waste; to squander; to exhaust;
<as>as, to <ex>spend</ex> an estate in gaming or other
vices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To pass, as time; to suffer to pass away; <as>as, to
<ex>spend</ex> a day idly; to <ex>spend</ex> winter
abroad</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We <qex>spend</qex> our years as a tale that is told.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. xc. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To exhaust of force or strength; to waste; to wear
away; <as>as, the violence of the waves was
<ex>spent</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their bodies <qex>spent</qex> with long labor and thirst.</q>
<rj><qau>Knolles.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spend</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spend
<hw>Spend</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To expend
money or any other possession; to consume, use, waste, or part with,
anything; <as>as, he who gets easily <ex>spends</ex>
freely</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>spends</qex> as a person who knows that he must come to a
reckoning.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To waste or wear away; to be consumed; to lose force
or strength; to vanish; <as>as, energy <ex>spends</ex> in the using of
it</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sound <qex>spendeth</qex> and is dissipated in the open
air.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be diffused; to spread.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The vines that they use for wine are so often cut, that their sap
<qex>spendeth</qex> into the grapes.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>To break ground; to continue
working.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spender</ent>⟦br⟧
